> Although we love a gooey, stick-to-your-ribs sort of mac 'n' cheese, sometimes you
> want a version that offers all of the same comforts but with a lighter, brighter
> feel to it. This recipe does just that, folding some crispy roasted cauliflower
> into the mix, adding a dash of warm North African spices, and introducing a
> cheese sauce that's creamy without feeling weighed down. If the bright orange
> mac is an occasional treat, this is one you can enjoy any night of the week.

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat #oven to 425
degrees. Bring a #large pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Toss @cauliflower florets{10%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season with
@salt{}, @pepper{}, and @Turkish spice blend{1/2%tsp} (we'll use more later).

Roast cauliflower in #oven until tender and lightly browned, about ~{25%minutes}.
Thinly slice @scallions{2}, keeping greens and whites separate. Halve, peel, and
finely chop @yellow onion{1}.

Once water is boiling, add @gemelli pasta{6%ounce} to #pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-12%minutes}, then drain.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (use an ovenproof pan
if you have one). Add onion and scallion whites. Cook, tossing, until softened,
~{3-5%minutes}. Stir in another @Turkish spice blend{1/2%tsp} (you'll have some
left over) and cook until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}. Sprinkle @flour{1%tbsp}
into pan and cook, stirring, until it loses its raw smell, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Slowly whisk @milk{1%cup} into pan (we sent more). Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{1} and bring to a simmer. Let bubble until thickened, about ~{2%minutes}.
Remove from heat and add @Italian cheese blend{1%cup}, stirring to melt. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir gemelli and cauliflower into pan. Transfer pan to #oven and bake until
crisp on top, about ~{5%minutes}. Toss @mixed greens{2%ounce} with
@balsamic vinegar{5%tsp} and a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #large bowl{}.
Divide pasta between plates and sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve salad on
the side.